            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A response to various questions about mystical and
                     esoteric matters posed by al-Tirmidhī (d. 285/898) in his famous work, Khatm
                     al-awliyāʾ (Seal of the Saints). It consists of 55 questions and answers. A
                     similar section is included in FM 2:39-139, but according to Michel Chodkiewicz
                     it is not identical to this work.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 11 mss., the best being Veliyuddin 1759, which is a
                  holograph, undated but necessarily before 638H. OY dates the composition as 603H
                  based on a note on Beyazit 3750 (253b), but we could not find any indication of
                  this; it looks as if there has been confusion with another work in the same
                  collection.</note>
